counterpoint : free trade involve a principle of free will . the buyer should be able to decide to whom he wish to sell and on what term , and if the seller do not accept those term then the buyer should be able to refuse to deal with him . manufacturers can have many good reason for choose to price good at different level in different country , such a their wish to build a long term brand preference by cheap initial marketing in a develop economy , or their desire to maintain an aura of exclusivity in mature market through high pricing and confine sale to specialist retailer . grey import result in the manufacturer distributor effectively lose some , and often most , control of their pricing and retailing strategy in the importing country . this reduce their capacity to position the brand a they see appropriate . in extremis , a company can be put out of business in one nation by it own operation overseas ! 
